name: String
description: Contains methods for the String primitive data type.

abbreviate(integer).name: abbreviate
abbreviate(integer).description: Returns an abbreviated version of the String, of the specified length and with ellipses appended if the current String is longer than the specified length; otherwise, returns the original String without ellipses.

abbreviate(integer,integer).name: abbreviate
abbreviate(integer,integer).signature: public String abbreviate(Integer maxWidth, Integer offset)
abbreviate(integer,integer).description: Returns an abbreviated version of the String, starting at the specified character offset and of the specified length. The returned String has ellipses appended at the start and the end if characters have been removed at these locations.

capitalize().name: capitalize
capitalize().description: Returns the current String with the first letter changed to title case.

center(integer).name: center
center(integer).description: Returns a version of the current String of the specified size padded with spaces on the left and right, so that it appears in the center. If the specified size is smaller than the current String size, the entire String is returned without added spaces.

center(integer,string).name: center
center(integer,string).signature: public String center(Integer size, String paddingString)
center(integer,string).description: Returns a version of the current String of the specified size padded with the specified String on the left and right, so that it appears in the center. If the specified size is smaller than the current String size, the entire String is returned without padding.

charat(integer).name: charAt
charat(integer).description: Returns the value of the character at the specified index.

codepointat(integer).name: codePointAt
codepointat(integer).description: Returns the Unicode code point value at the specified index.

codepointbefore(integer).name: codePointBefore
codepointbefore(integer).description: Returns the Unicode code point value that occurs before the specified index.

codepointcount(integer,integer).name: codePointCount
codepointcount(integer,integer).signature: public Integer codePointCount(Integer beginIndex, Integer endIndex)
codepointcount(integer,integer).description: Returns the number of Unicode code points within the specified text range.

compareto(string).name: compareTo
compareto(string).description: Compares two strings lexicographically, based on the Unicode value of each character in the Strings.

contains(string).name: contains
contains(string).description: Returns true if and only if the String that called the method contains the specified sequence of characters in substring.

containsany(string).name: containsAny
containsany(string).description: Returns true if the current String contains any of the characters in the specified String; otherwise, returns false.

containsignorecase(string).name: containsIgnoreCase
containsignorecase(string).description: Returns true if the current String contains the specified sequence of characters without regard to case; otherwise, returns false.

containsnone(string).name: containsNone
containsnone(string).description: Returns true if the current String doesn’t contain any of the characters in the specified String; otherwise, returns false.

containsonly(string).name: containsOnly
containsonly(string).description: Returns true if the current String contains characters only from the specified sequence of characters and not any other characters; otherwise, returns false.

containswhitespace().name: containsWhitespace
containswhitespace().description: Returns true if the current String contains any white space characters; otherwise, returns false.

countmatches(string).name: countMatches
countmatches(string).description: Returns the number of times the specified substring occurs in the current String.

deletewhitespace().name: deleteWhitespace
deletewhitespace().description: Returns a version of the current String with all white space characters removed.

difference(string).name: difference
difference(string).description: Returns the difference between the current String and the specified String.

endswith(string).name: endsWith
endswith(string).description: Returns true if the String that called the method ends with the specified suffix.

endswithignorecase(string).name: endsWithIgnoreCase
endswithignorecase(string).description: Returns true if the current String ends with the specified suffix; otherwise, returns false.

equals(string).name: equals
equals(string).description: Deprecated. This method is replaced by equals(stringOrId). Returns true if the passed-in string is not null and represents the same binary sequence of characters as the current string. Use this method to perform case-sensitive comparisons.

equals(object).name: equals
equals(object).description: Returns true if the passed-in object is not null and represents the same binary sequence of characters as the current string. Use this method to compare a string to an object that represents a string or an ID.

equalsignorecase(string).name: equalsIgnoreCase
equalsignorecase(string).description: Returns true if the secondString is not null and represents the same sequence of characters as the String that called the method, ignoring case.

escapecsv().name: escapeCsv
escapecsv().description: Returns a String for a CSV column enclosed in double quotes, if required.

escapeecmascript().name: escapeEcmaScript
escapeecmascript().description: Escapes the characters in the String using EcmaScript String rules.

escapehtml3().name: escapeHtml3
escapehtml3().description: Escapes the characters in a String using HTML 3.0 entities.

escapehtml4().name: escapeHtml4
escapehtml4().description: Escapes the characters in a String using HTML 4.0 entities.

escapejava().name: escapeJava
escapejava().description: Returns a String whose characters are escaped using Java String rules. Characters escaped include quotes and control characters, such as tab, backslash, and carriage return characters.

escapesinglequotes(string).name: escapeSingleQuotes
escapesinglequotes(string).description: Returns a String with the escape character (\) added before any single quotation marks in the String s.

escapeunicode().name: escapeUnicode
escapeunicode().description: Returns a String whose Unicode characters are escaped to a Unicode escape sequence.

escapexml().name: escapeXml
escapexml().description: Escapes the characters in a String using XML entities.

format(string,list).name: format
format(string,list).signature: public static String format(String stringToFormat, List <Object>)
format(string,list).description: Treat the first argument as a pattern and return a string using the second argument for substitution and formatting. The substitution and formatting are the same as apex:outputText and the Java MessageFormat class. Non-string types in the second argument’s List are implicitly converted to strings, respecting the toString() method overrides that exist on the type.

fromchararray(list).name: fromCharArray
fromchararray(list).description: Returns a String from the values of the list of integers.

getchars().name: getChars
getchars().description: Returns an array of character values that represent the characters in this string.

getcommonprefix(list).name: getCommonPrefix
getcommonprefix(list).description: Returns the initial sequence of characters as a String that is common to all the specified Strings.

getlevenshteindistance(string).name: getLevenshteinDistance
getlevenshteindistance(string).description: Returns the Levenshtein distance between the current String and the specified String.

getlevenshteindistance(string,integer).name: getLevenshteinDistance
getlevenshteindistance(string,integer).signature: public Integer getLevenshteinDistance(String stringToCompare, Integer threshold)
getlevenshteindistance(string,integer).description: Returns the Levenshtein distance between the current String and the specified String if it is less than or equal than the given threshold; otherwise, returns -1.

hashcode().name: hashCode
hashcode().description: Returns a hash code value for this string.

indexof(string).name: indexOf
indexof(string).description: Returns the index of the first occurrence of the specified substring. If the substring does not occur, this method returns -1.

indexof(string,integer).name: indexOf
indexof(string,integer).signature: public Integer indexOf(String substring, Integer index)
indexof(string,integer).description: Returns the zero-based index of the first occurrence of the specified substring from the point of the given index. If the substring does not occur, this method returns -1.

indexofany(string).name: indexOfAny
indexofany(string).description: Returns the zero-based index of the first occurrence of any character specified in the substring. If none of the characters occur, returns -1.

indexofanybut(string).name: indexOfAnyBut
indexofanybut(string).description: Returns the zero-based index of the first occurrence of a character that is not in the specified substring. Otherwise, returns -1.

indexofchar(integer).name: indexOfChar
indexofchar(integer).description: Returns the index of the first occurrence of the character that corresponds to the specified character value.

indexofchar(integer,integer).name: indexOfChar
indexofchar(integer,integer).signature: public Integer indexOfChar(Integer character, Integer startIndex)
indexofchar(integer,integer).description: Returns the index of the first occurrence of the character that corresponds to the specified character value, starting from the specified index.

indexofdifference(string).name: indexOfDifference
indexofdifference(string).description: Returns the zero-based index of the character where the current String begins to differ from the specified String.

indexofignorecase(string).name: indexOfIgnoreCase
indexofignorecase(string).description: Returns the zero-based index of the first occurrence of the specified substring without regard to case. If the substring does not occur, this method returns -1.

indexofignorecase(string,integer).name: indexOfIgnoreCase
indexofignorecase(string,integer).signature: public Integer indexOfIgnoreCase(String substring, Integer startPosition)
indexofignorecase(string,integer).description: Returns the zero-based index of the first occurrence of the specified substring from the point of index i, without regard to case. If the substring does not occur, this method returns -1.

isalllowercase().name: isAllLowerCase
isalllowercase().description: Returns true if all characters in the current String are lowercase; otherwise, returns false.

isalluppercase().name: isAllUpperCase
isalluppercase().description: Returns true if all characters in the current String are uppercase; otherwise, returns false.

isalpha().name: isAlpha
isalpha().description: Returns true if all characters in the current String are Unicode letters only; otherwise, returns false.

isalphaspace().name: isAlphaSpace
isalphaspace().description: Returns true if all characters in the current String are Unicode letters or spaces only; otherwise, returns false.

isalphanumeric().name: isAlphanumeric
isalphanumeric().description: Returns true if all characters in the current String are Unicode letters or numbers only; otherwise, returns false.

isalphanumericspace().name: isAlphanumericSpace
isalphanumericspace().description: Returns true if all characters in the current String are Unicode letters, numbers, or spaces only; otherwise, returns false.

isasciiprintable().name: isAsciiPrintable
isasciiprintable().description: Returns true if the current String contains only ASCII printable characters; otherwise, returns false.

isblank(string).name: isBlank
isblank(string).description: Returns true if the specified String is white space, empty (''), or null; otherwise, returns false.

isempty(string).name: isEmpty
isempty(string).description: Returns true if the specified String is empty ('') or null; otherwise, returns false.

isnotblank(string).name: isNotBlank
isnotblank(string).description: Returns true if the specified String is not whitespace, not empty (''), and not null; otherwise, returns false.

isnotempty(string).name: isNotEmpty
isnotempty(string).description: Returns true if the specified String is not empty ('') and not null; otherwise, returns false.

isnumeric().name: isNumeric
isnumeric().description: Returns true if the current String contains only Unicode digits; otherwise, returns false.

isnumericspace().name: isNumericSpace
isnumericspace().description: Returns true if the current String contains only Unicode digits or spaces; otherwise, returns false.

iswhitespace().name: isWhitespace
iswhitespace().description: Returns true if the current String contains only white space characters or is empty; otherwise, returns false.

join(object,string).name: join
join(object,string).signature: public static String join(Object iterableObj, String separator)
join(object,string).description: Joins the elements of the specified iterable object, such as a List, into a single String separated by the specified separator.

lastindexof(string).name: lastIndexOf
lastindexof(string).description: Returns the index of the last occurrence of the specified substring. If the substring does not occur, this method returns -1.

lastindexof(string,integer).name: lastIndexOf
lastindexof(string,integer).signature: public Integer lastIndexOf(String substring, Integer endPosition)
lastindexof(string,integer).description: Returns the index of the last occurrence of the specified substring, starting from the character at index 0 and ending at the specified index.

lastindexofchar(integer).name: lastIndexOfChar
lastindexofchar(integer).description: Returns the index of the last occurrence of the character that corresponds to the specified character value.

lastindexofchar(integer,integer).name: lastIndexOfChar
lastindexofchar(integer,integer).signature: public Integer lastIndexOfChar(Integer character, Integer endIndex)
lastindexofchar(integer,integer).description: Returns the index of the last occurrence of the character that corresponds to the specified character value, starting from the specified index.

lastindexofignorecase(string).name: lastIndexOfIgnoreCase
lastindexofignorecase(string).description: Returns the index of the last occurrence of the specified substring regardless of case.

lastindexofignorecase(string,integer).name: lastIndexOfIgnoreCase
lastindexofignorecase(string,integer).signature: public Integer lastIndexOfIgnoreCase(String substring, Integer endPosition)
lastindexofignorecase(string,integer).description: Returns the index of the last occurrence of the specified substring regardless of case, starting from the character at index 0 and ending at the specified index.

left(integer).name: left
left(integer).description: Returns the leftmost characters of the current String of the specified length.

leftpad(integer).name: leftPad
leftpad(integer).description: Returns the current String padded with spaces on the left and of the specified length.

leftpad(integer,string).name: leftPad
leftpad(integer,string).signature: public String leftPad(Integer length, String padStr)
leftpad(integer,string).description: Returns the current String padded with String padStr on the left and of the specified length.

length().name: length
length().description: Returns the number of 16-bit Unicode characters contained in the String.

mid(integer,integer).name: mid
mid(integer,integer).signature: public String mid(Integer startIndex, Integer length)
mid(integer,integer).description: Returns a new String that begins with the character at the specified zero-based startIndex with the number of characters specified by length.

normalizespace().name: normalizeSpace
normalizespace().description: Returns the current String with leading, trailing, and repeating white space characters removed.

offsetbycodepoints(integer,integer).name: offsetByCodePoints
offsetbycodepoints(integer,integer).signature: public Integer offsetByCodePoints(Integer index, Integer codePointOffset)
offsetbycodepoints(integer,integer).description: Returns the index of the Unicode code point that is offset by the specified number of code points, starting from the given index.

remove(string).name: remove
remove(string).description: Removes all occurrences of the specified substring and returns the String result.

removeend(string).name: removeEnd
removeend(string).description: Removes the specified substring only if it occurs at the end of the String.

removeendignorecase(string).name: removeEndIgnoreCase
removeendignorecase(string).description: Removes the specified substring only if it occurs at the end of the String using a case-insensitive match.

removestart(string).name: removeStart
removestart(string).description: Removes the specified substring only if it occurs at the beginning of the String.

removestartignorecase(string).name: removeStartIgnoreCase
removestartignorecase(string).description: Removes the specified substring only if it occurs at the beginning of the String using a case-insensitive match.

repeat(integer).name: repeat
repeat(integer).description: Returns the current String repeated the specified number of times.

repeat(string,integer).name: repeat
repeat(string,integer).signature: public String repeat(String separator, Integer numberOfTimes)
repeat(string,integer).description: Returns the current String repeated the specified number of times using the specified separator to separate the repeated Strings.

replace(string,string).name: replace
replace(string,string).signature: public String replace(String target, String replacement)
replace(string,string).description: Replaces each substring of a string that matches the literal target sequence target with the specified literal replacement sequence replacement.

replaceall(string,string).name: replaceAll
replaceall(string,string).signature: public String replaceAll(String regExp, String replacement)
replaceall(string,string).description: Replaces each substring of a string that matches the regular expression regExp with the replacement sequence replacement.

replacefirst(string,string).name: replaceFirst
replacefirst(string,string).signature: public String replaceFirst(String regExp, String replacement)
replacefirst(string,string).description: Replaces the first substring of a string that matches the regular expression regExp with the replacement sequence replacement.

reverse().name: reverse
reverse().description: Returns a String with all the characters reversed.

right(integer).name: right
right(integer).description: Returns the rightmost characters of the current String of the specified length.

rightpad(integer).name: rightPad
rightpad(integer).description: Returns the current String padded with spaces on the right and of the specified length.

rightpad(integer,string).name: rightPad
rightpad(integer,string).signature: public String rightPad(Integer length, String padStr)
rightpad(integer,string).description: Returns the current String padded with String padStr on the right and of the specified length.

split(string).name: split
split(string).description: Returns a list that contains each substring of the String that is terminated by either the regular expression regExp or the end of the String.

split(string,integer).name: split
split(string,integer).signature: public String[] split(String regExp, Integer limit)
split(string,integer).description: Returns a list that contains each substring of the String that is terminated by either the regular expression regExp or the end of the String.

splitbycharactertype().name: splitByCharacterType
splitbycharactertype().description: Splits the current String by character type and returns a list of contiguous character groups of the same type as complete tokens.

splitbycharactertypecamelcase().name: splitByCharacterTypeCamelCase
splitbycharactertypecamelcase().description: Splits the current String by character type and returns a list of contiguous character groups of the same type as complete tokens, with the following exception: the uppercase character, if any, immediately preceding a lowercase character token belongs to the following character token rather than to the preceding.

startswith(string).name: startsWith
startswith(string).description: Returns true if the String that called the method begins with the specified prefix.

startswithignorecase(string).name: startsWithIgnoreCase
startswithignorecase(string).description: Returns true if the current String begins with the specified prefix regardless of the prefix case.

striphtmltags(string).name: stripHtmlTags
striphtmltags(string).description: Removes HTML markup and returns plain text.

substring(integer).name: substring
substring(integer).description: Returns a new String that begins with the character at the specified zero-based startIndex and extends to the end of the String.

substring(integer,integer).name: substring
substring(integer,integer).signature: public String substring(Integer startIndex, Integer endIndex)
substring(integer,integer).description: Returns a new String that begins with the character at the specified zero-based startIndex and extends to the character at endIndex - 1.

substringafter(string).name: substringAfter
substringafter(string).description: Returns the substring that occurs after the first occurrence of the specified separator.

substringafterlast(string).name: substringAfterLast
substringafterlast(string).description: Returns the substring that occurs after the last occurrence of the specified separator.

substringbefore(string).name: substringBefore
substringbefore(string).description: Returns the substring that occurs before the first occurrence of the specified separator.

substringbeforelast(string).name: substringBeforeLast
substringbeforelast(string).description: Returns the substring that occurs before the last occurrence of the specified separator.

substringbetween(string).name: substringBetween
substringbetween(string).description: Returns the substring that occurs between two instances of the specified tag String.

substringbetween(string,string).name: substringBetween
substringbetween(string,string).signature: public String substringBetween(String open, String close)
substringbetween(string,string).description: Returns the substring that occurs between the two specified Strings.

swapcase().name: swapCase
swapcase().description: Swaps the case of all characters and returns the resulting String by using the default (English US) locale.

tolowercase().name: toLowerCase
tolowercase().description: Converts all of the characters in the String to lowercase using the rules of the default (English US) locale.

tolowercase(string).name: toLowerCase
tolowercase(string).description: Converts all of the characters in the String to lowercase using the rules of the specified locale.

touppercase().name: toUpperCase
touppercase().description: Converts all of the characters in the String to uppercase using the rules of the default (English US) locale.

touppercase(string).name: toUpperCase
touppercase(string).description: Converts all of the characters in the String to the uppercase using the rules of the specified locale.

trim().name: trim
trim().description: Returns a copy of the string that no longer contains any leading or trailing white space characters.

uncapitalize().name: uncapitalize
uncapitalize().description: Returns the current String with the first letter in lowercase.

unescapecsv().name: unescapeCsv
unescapecsv().description: Returns a String representing an unescaped CSV column.

unescapeecmascript().name: unescapeEcmaScript
unescapeecmascript().description: Unescapes any EcmaScript literals found in the String.

unescapehtml3().name: unescapeHtml3
unescapehtml3().description: Unescapes the characters in a String using HTML 3.0 entities.

unescapehtml4().name: unescapeHtml4
unescapehtml4().description: Unescapes the characters in a String using HTML 4.0 entities.

unescapejava().name: unescapeJava
unescapejava().description: Returns a String whose Java literals are unescaped. Literals unescaped include escape sequences for quotes (\\") and control characters, such as tab (\\t), and carriage return (\\n).

unescapeunicode().name: unescapeUnicode
unescapeunicode().description: Returns a String whose escaped Unicode characters are unescaped.

unescapexml().name: unescapeXml
unescapexml().description: Unescapes the characters in a String using XML entities.

valueof(date).name: valueOf
valueof(date).description: Returns a String that represents the specified Date in the standard “yyyy-MM-dd” format.

valueof(datetime).name: valueOf
valueof(datetime).description: Returns a String that represents the specified Datetime in the standard “yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss” format for the local time zone.

valueof(decimal).name: valueOf
valueof(decimal).description: Returns a String that represents the specified Decimal.

valueof(double).name: valueOf
valueof(double).description: Returns a String that represents the specified Double.

valueof(integer).name: valueOf
valueof(integer).description: Returns a String that represents the specified Integer.

valueof(long).name: valueOf
valueof(long).description: Returns a String that represents the specified Long.

valueof(object).name: valueOf
valueof(object).description: Returns a string representation of the specified object argument.

valueofgmt(datetime).name: valueOfGmt
valueofgmt(datetime).description: Returns a String that represents the specified Datetime in the standard “yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss” format for the GMT time zone.
